<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>Primary Statute:</strong> Companies Act 2013.</p>
                <p><strong>Charging Section:</strong> Section 14 - Alteration of articles; contains the proviso that any alteration having the effect of conversion of a public company into a private company shall not be valid unless approved by an order of the Central Government.</p>
                <p><strong>Related Sections:</strong> Section 13 (alteration of Memorandum); Section 18 (conversion of companies already registered); Section 114 (special resolution); Section 117 (filing of resolutions).</p>
                <p><strong>Procedural Rules:</strong> Rule 41 of Companies (Incorporation) Rules 2014 - prescribes the full conversion workflow.</p>
                <p><strong>Delegation:</strong> Section 14 proviso power vested in Central Government; delegated to Regional Director through Notification SO 6225(E) dated 18 December 2018 issued post the Companies (Amendment) Act 2019.</p>
                <p><strong>Pre-Amendment Position:</strong> Prior to Companies (Amendment) Act 2019, the power was exercised by the National Company Law Tribunal (NCLT); the amendment shifted the power to the Central Government to expedite the process.</p>
                <p><strong>Private Limited Definition:</strong> Section 2(68) Companies Act 2013 - (a) restricts right to transfer shares, (b) limits members to 200 (excluding past and present employees who became members during employment), (c) prohibits invitation to public for subscription.</p>
                <p><strong>Special Resolution Threshold:</strong> Section 114(2) - 75% of members present and voting at the EGM; requires 21 clear days of EGM notice.</p>
                <p><strong>MGT-14 Filing:</strong> Section 117 - within 30 days of passing the special resolution.</p>
                <p><strong>Newspaper Publication:</strong> Rule 41(2) - Form INC-25A in one English daily and one vernacular daily circulating in the company's registered office state.</p>
                <p><strong>Individual Creditor Notice:</strong> Rule 41(3) - Form INC-26 served on every creditor and debenture holder of the company.</p>
                <p><strong>Objection Window:</strong> 21 days from the date of publication of the newspaper advertisement and service of individual notices.</p>
                <p><strong>Form RD-1 Filing:</strong> Application to Regional Director - filed within 60 days of the special resolution.</p>
                <p><strong>Bar on Conversion:</strong> Rule 41(5) - conversion not permitted if the company is under any ongoing investigation, inspection or prosecution.</p>
                <p><strong>RD Hearing:</strong> Where objections are received, Regional Director schedules a hearing within 30 days; documented in affidavit.</p>
                <p><strong>Form INC-28 Filing:</strong> Filing of the Regional Director order with the ROC within 15 days of receipt.</p>
                <p><strong>Listed Company Precondition:</strong> Listed Public Limited Companies must first complete SEBI delisting under SEBI (Delisting of Equity Shares) Regulations 2021 before initiating Section 14 conversion.</p>
                <p><strong>Post-Conversion Carryforward:</strong> Section 18 - assets, liabilities, contracts, pending legal proceedings, ongoing tax positions all carry forward; body corporate continues with the same CIN modified for company type.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority - Conversion Approval:</strong> Regional Director (Northern Region), Ministry of Corporate Affairs, Lok Nayak Bhawan, Khan Market, New Delhi 110003 (for companies registered in Delhi, Haryana, Punjab, Himachal Pradesh, J&K, Chandigarh, Ladakh).</p>
                <p><strong>Authority - Company Filings:</strong> Registrar of Companies (ROC), NCT of Delhi and Haryana, CGO Complex, Lodhi Road, New Delhi 110003.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> MCA21 v3 at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a>, SEBI at <a href="https://www.sebi.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">sebi.gov.in</a> and India Code (statutes) at <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">indiacode.nic.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

